1943;;Reveille with Beverly;;American;;Charles Barton;;Ann Miller, Franklin Pangborn, Larry Parks;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reveille_with_Beverly;;Beverly Ross (Ann Miller) wants to be a radio personality, but has to run the switchboard at a local station. The blustery station owner Mr. Kennedy (Tim Ryan) wants no part of programming the "jive that she loves", preferring the classics.[3]After struggling to keep her time slot, Beverly broadcasts her show from an Army base.[4]